<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-02-05T16:04:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-02-05T16:04:00-05:00" n="912" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d912">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No.2812.00/2742.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at
                                    Chihuahua</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.—Extracts.—Paraphrases.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Chihuahua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-02-05T14:00:00-07:04">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 5, 1912—2 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The State is a unit against the Federal Government, and open war will
                            follow entrance any Federal troops into the State. Control of leaders
                            over soldiers problematical and civil authorities helpless.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Letcher.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>